tember 1323","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"en":{"about 1280–before 1349":"about 1280–before 1349","1280–1349":"1280–1349","1284–1323":"1284–1323","1302–1348":"1302–1348","1304–1376":"1304–1376","1306–Female":"1306–Deceased","1308–1344":"1308–1344","1260–Male":"1260–Deceased","1260–Female":"1260–Deceased","before 28 August 1344":"before 28 August 1344","1284":"1284","1260":"1260","before 1349":"before 1349","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","before 20 November 1301":"before 20 November 1301","1453":"1453","1376":"1376","1317":"1317","about 1280":"about 1280","1290":"1290","1349":"1349","1348":"1348","1304":"1304","about 1308":"about 1308","1302":"1302","1323":"1323","about 1306":"about 1306","1344":"1344","about 1304":"about 1304","about 1302":"about 1302","before 27 September 1323":"before 27 September 1323","1308":"1308","1328":"1328","1306":"1306","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":10,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705191,"age":35,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":48,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":57,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor was born about 1280, in Lincolnshire, England, her father, John Ferrers of Tothill, was 21 and her mother, Miss John Ferre, was 22. She married Sir Ralph Gorges 1st Baron before 20 November 1301, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 3 daughters. She died befor